sql:
SELECT directors.name AS director_name, films.title AS film_title
FROM films
INNER JOIN directors ON films.director_id = directors.director_id;

external_knowledge:
- "ocean waves" is a metaphor for 'genre_name';
- "surfers" is a metaphor for 'shot_count';
- "master wave riders" is a metaphor for 'director_name';
- The metaphorical expression 'carrying the most surfers' refers to a high number of shots associated with a genre;
- 'skillfully maneuvering' implies the directors are effectively managing the shots in their films.

- "cinematic masterpieces" metaphorically refers to film titles; 
- "types of shots" relates to shot_type_name; 
- "insights gained from each cinematic stroke" signifies the analysis_type and its result;
- "organized by the tales they tell" means the results will be ordered by the film titles.

- "cinematic blossoms" refers to films that have been produced and released during a specific period;
- "turn of the millennium to the years of the teens" refers to the years between 2000 and 2010;
- "attracted the most detailed examination under the microscope of analysis" implies the films with the highest number of analyses performed on their shots;
- "visionary directors" refers to the directors of those films.

